rComments: I don't understand why he has such a high rating! He was okay, but his tone was too monotonous, and the dim lights in the classroom, combined with his language, made people drowsy. He obviously can upload some PDFs to Brightspace for free, but he insists that students spend 50 Canadian dollars to buy them, speechless!

Loved him! Super easygoing and available outside of class. The content is very interesting and he's able to teach a subject from many perspectives. Also is really able to engage with the class. Not a tough grader and is always super clear about his expectations.
Very knowledgeable and lenient professor who is clear in what he wants for assignments. Would definitely take again.

This guy is the god of teaching. Tells u how to study for exams but its usually the tAs who correct ur work. Managed to keep me focused through a 7-10 which is crazy to say. Pay attention in class and do the readings and ur set. Although he can be specific for the exams but if you put in the work ur guaranteed a good grade.

Super smart and nice guy, but the class he was teaching was absolutely horrible. As it was his first time teaching it, so much of the content was dry, irrelevant, super complicated and hard-to-follow. I guess it's a lot asking for a prof to make a research methods course fun, but I went to every class all semester and didn't really listen at all...

Lectures are SUPER heavy and are bone-dry. The subject matter is pretty easy to comprehend, but holy hell is there a lot of readings for this class. This was his first time teaching the course, so its a work in progress and he seems to be improving it. The slide shows are just chunks of texts, and his notes rarely deviate from them.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Litterally attended two classes in the whole semester. ALTHOUGH the prof seems amazingly nice, and I could tell that he's doing his best. The class was 7-10pm and very heavy in theory and in readings. As I said, the teacher seems great though.
He's a good professor, it is just the class itself that is horrible: the material covered. He knows his stuff well but the course itself is very dry.

McMillan clearly cares about teaching and is very engaged as a professor. The only downside is the class itself. An almost obscene amount of readings and not very clear grading criteria make this course difficult. The lectures, while full of enthusiasm, are very dry and the concepts are simple which makes keeping interest in the class difficult.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Had him for a seminar so obviously reading heavy, but they were usually fairly interesting. Prof is a great guy, and often brought treats for the class. Participate and you will do well! But talk to him if you have anxiety and can't. Takes an insane amount of time to get assignments back, so if that matters to you don't take his class.

From my experience Professor McMillan cares a lot about his students and tries his best to make sure everyone understands the material. You might have to wait longer than normal to get your grades back but it ends up being worth it because his feedback is genuine and useful. Great guy!
Great Prof, his classes can be theoretical at times, but just do the readings, ask questions and go over PowerPoint and you will do fine!

His lectures were very theory heavy, which made it pretty dry sometimes. However, you can tell that he really likes what he is teaching. He was very approachable and always gave helpful answers to emails about assignments. You do need to do some readings for the exams. All in all I would definitely recommend him as a teacher.

A personally challenging course because of the inanity of (generally) d-u-m-b, convoluted IR Theory. The second half of the course was much more concrete/less theoretical and more enjoyable. More importantly, MacMillan is BAE. Very clear in his explanations and expectations. He's a very fair and helpful prof. B A E.

He is the best prof! Super interesting lectures, took topics I knew nothing about and explained them perfectly! Never boring, and willing to give extensions if you email him. Only downside was that the assignment was really tough and took a long time. Tests were pretty easy but have to do his at least three of the course pack readings.

One of my favourite classes of uni, there is a lot of readings but McMillan spends the class going through them and explaining them and discussing them. He gives extremely good feedback on all assignments/tests. He's also an extremely approachable and flexible guy regarding anything. He's extremely theoretical in his teaching approach.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures ', 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: such a great prof! he makes his lectures interesting and is always joking around which is refreshing! you can tell he really cares about his students success. definitely  recommend any class with him!

McMillan is an awesome professor. In both courses I've taken he conveys the material VERY clearly and is so helpful outside of class. This semester he met with the class for three hours over dinner to review the entirety of the readings before the exam. Few Profs would do that and it was much appreciated. I absolutely recommend any classes with him

McMillan is an amazing professor. He is very clear and thorough in his explanations of difficult theoretical concepts. He doesn't assume that we know everything just because we are in a 4th year seminar. He pushed back the essay outline and final essay due dates to help out the students. He takes a while to correct but his feedback is very helpful.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Prof McMillan is phenomenal. He understands that his course content can be dry and does an amazing job at keeping it fresh and breaking down concepts for us. He held multiple optional DGDs for reviews before the midterm and final and his exams very closely reflect the material covered in class. He even kept me awake in an 8:30. 10/10!!

Amazing prof, absolutely loved his class. All his lectures are interesting and super great for the midterms and exam. Long final essay but he makes it clear and breaks it down for you, so it becomes very easy to write. Would recommend this class to anyone!!

Had him for POL2103! Extremely clear and communicative and caring about concerns the student may have. I was genuinely impressed by his efforts to make sure students understand and I found that very inspiring. He's humble, sincere, works hard and has a wonderful smile! Overall a very fair professor. Would love to take him again!
All around great guy, interesting lectures, explains everything clearly, answers emails quickly. Highly recommend, he's such a good prof. Learned so much in his class. THANK YOU

Kevin McMillan is an excellent professor! Although course material can be dry, he does his best to make it relevant and interesting. Extremely helpful during office hours and responds to emails quickly. Really nice guy and an overall beauty.
Great prof, conveys material very effectively.  He's personable, relatable and is willing to assist during office hours.

Really nice guy and had good lectures with slides that he elaborated on. The paper was quite long but he was extremely helpful if contacted. The readings are long but ESSENTIAL to read as they need to be referenced in the midterm and exam. You really need to know the course material to do well.

Fantastic as always. Professor McMillan is one of the best Professors at uOttawa. Incredibly knowledgeable and genuinely cares about helping you to understand and learn the material. His courses aren't easy (and he very rarely gives grades above an 8), but they are 100% worth it. Take a course with him if you can!

Lectures are interesting, readings are directly relevant to the course material, and the assignments keep you firmly attached to the theories taught in the course. Light atmosphere and easy-going tone during class promotes a healthy learning environment. You will read a lot. But welcome to IR. That's the name of the game.

Amazing lecturer and is always there to help you. The examinations are really fairly marked and are easy to prepare for. The paper is long but is extremely structured and simple to do with some decent amount of effort. If you stay on task, getting a good mark is not hard at all.

I would recommend this class to anyone who wants a basic knowledge about International Relations. McMillan is a great guy. Very understanding of issues that arise with his assignments as he understands that they are not always easy to do. 17 page paper in this class, so start early. Gives great powerpoints and review classes are great for exams.

Great lecturer. He speaks from the heart. Seems to know absolutely everything in the world. You just want to stare at him in awe. Fair midterms. He's amazing. He's also extremely helpful and encourages everyone to email and visit him. I asked one question and he wrote me back 4 paragraphs to make sure I understood. He's also very handsome.

He is probably the best professor I've had throughout my university experience. Very informative discussions. Really knows his material. His marking is very fair. More importantly he conveys the information in a coherent, comprehensible, and interesting manner. If you can, I strongly urge everyone to take his course, just be prepared to read a lot
Great prof! Made the subject interesting. Lots of feedback on assignments. Course does require work.
what a good prof. super super helpful and leaves tons of useful comments on assignments. not an easy class, though, but highly recommend him as a professor
He is extremely helpful. Very clear about his expectations, always give long feedback. Can be a bit slow in terms of marking. Not the easiest prof, but you learn a lot in his class. LOVE HIS SMILE
SO UNORGANIZED!!!!!! knows his stuff though

Really good professor. I now love international relations after taking his class. It may not be for everybody and his lectures can be dense, but if you are actually interested in learning and studying in university then I don't think you would be disappointed. You will learn a lot in his class if you want to.

I found him to be very well organized and explained all materials required for exams very clearly. He regularly uses virtual campus to answer questions about assignments or lectures and is overall a great prof.

A bit disorganized in structuring his DGDs, but he's a decent lecturer, very helpful with assignments, and uses Virtual Campus regularly to assist students. I'm personally not a fan of IR, so I found the material a bit dry but he's a good professor who genuinely cares about his students.

POL2103- Absolutely Loved!!!! Ive never been so interested in learning a polsci course. Hes super helpful, clear&wants to see his students do their best. Hes fair and understanding which I cant say for most of the profs at OU. Wish he taught summer! As long as you follow the material and dont slack youll do amazing!5star prof!

Honestly, the best proff I have ever had. He is always there to help you, responds asap, understanding, and truly helps his students LEARN and do their best. If i could id want him for every single class! :)

Didn't like the class at all, barely went, didn't go to my dgd's, but honestly the guy is there to help. So clear with what he wants. He gave an insane amount of information with respect to our 30% research proposal. Posted all the slides, research help, everything. Very clear in what he wants, and very helpful as well.

He was overall a great guy. He was unfortunately always late for every class including the midterm and the final. He never printed off enough exams to go around. But he was very understanding if you got mixed up on an assignment. His readings were too long and very theoretical. His lectures were as interesting as they could be for 8:30am.

Wants to see his students do well.  Makes good conversation in his lectures to help in understanding the material.  Wasn't very interested in the subject but would gladly take another class if he decides to teach something other than Int'l Rel.

LOVE Dr. McMillan. One of the best profs ever. Crystal clear lectures, which move at a perfect pace - fast enough to keep you stimulated, but not overwhelming. He draws in so many ideas into his explanations of IR - historical context, and even aspects of social psychology. He has mandatory DGDs; try to get into HIS DGD instead of the TA ones.

Very clear. He goes off topic once in a while but it's always in response to a quesiton and in the end, if we dont cover something in class, he just takes it off the exam. Great guy. Great prof. Great Class.

I hate to give him a bad rating because he's a nice guy.  Lectures aren't terrible but he goes SO off topic.  The course was unfortunately very poorly organized and assignments were incomprehensible.  My TA basically had to pick up the slack for him... Avoid.

Nice prof. The readings are quite lengthy and theoretical but prof does a good job of exlaining readings in class and in mandatory DGD. Assigments and marking were fair. It was a challenging course but learned alot!
Very helpful and accessible. The classes are usually an in depth review of the texts that Kevin expresses a very deep understanding of. Has experience with both US and Canadian IR faculties.

He is an amazing prof who answers even the dumbest questions with a response that everyone can learn from. Seems like a really nice person and he explains everything really well... the only thing that sucked was the dgd which was mandatory

This is a professor who can really teach. IR is full of jargon and complex views of the world, but he manages to simplify the material really well. Extremely helpful and provides great feedback/comments (usually a long paragraph). He selects really interesting readings and expects an advanced level of critical analysis. A challenge, but worth it :)

heavy theoretical content and lots of weekly readings (discussed in weekly mandatory DGD). Fair marker but not overly generous. Funny Prof, clear expectations, overall nice guy :) Wants to see his students do well.
